Shared target directory lock mechanism: with-target-lock.sh implements reader/writer locking (shared for cargo tasks, exclusive for cleanup) to prevent races where one worktree's build:clean rm -rf's artifacts out from under another worktree's in-flight build; cleanup-stale-target.sh, typecheck.sh, and sync-versions.sh all invoke it with consistent mode and parameters to guard concurrent artifact access across worktrees.
